1
00:00:04,107 --> 00:00:05,075
(This drama is a work of fiction.)

2
00:00:05,075 --> 00:00:06,476
(All characters, organizations,
and events in this drama are fictitious.)

3
00:00:06,476 --> 00:00:07,544
(Scenes with child actors
followed production guidelines.)

4
00:00:07,577 --> 00:00:09,146
Please reconsider, Mr. Seong.

5
00:00:09,146 --> 00:00:11,581
We have nothing right now.

6
00:00:23,827 --> 00:00:24,861
My name is Seong Tae Hun.

7
00:00:25,395 --> 00:00:27,497
I fought my way here
by taking on one guy at a time.

8
00:00:29,232 --> 00:00:30,434
For the past 25 years,

9
00:00:31,201 --> 00:00:32,636
I bet my entire life...

10
00:00:33,637 --> 00:00:35,205
on this.

11
00:00:38,342 --> 00:00:39,242
Mr. Seong.

12
00:00:47,484 --> 00:00:49,820
(Director's Office)

13
00:00:57,260 --> 00:00:59,596
Napa cabbage.

14
00:01:04,868 --> 00:01:05,769
I...

15
00:01:06,436 --> 00:01:08,071
Hey, Mr. Seong.

16
00:01:08,739 --> 00:01:11,675
I was just climbing over
Cheonwang Peak on Jirisan.

17
00:01:11,675 --> 00:01:15,312
At this rate, my heart's going
to hike to heaven before I do.

18
00:01:16,313 --> 00:01:17,681
I told you already, sir.

19
00:01:18,081 --> 00:01:20,150
This napa cabbage...

20
00:01:20,517 --> 00:01:22,919
The raw ingredient, napa cabbage,
is the problem.

21
00:01:23,353 --> 00:01:25,289
Every time, the origin
of the main ingredient changes,

22
00:01:25,289 --> 00:01:27,024
so the taste of our kimchi
changes completely.

23
00:01:27,024 --> 00:01:29,359
So how are we supposed to build
loyal customers?

24
00:01:47,611 --> 00:01:48,545
Right.

25
00:01:48,779 --> 00:01:50,547
So when we think of napa cabbage,
who comes to mind?

26
00:01:50,714 --> 00:01:51,581
Pardon?

27
00:01:51,581 --> 00:01:54,184
You, the napa cabbage expert,
are right here.

28
00:01:54,651 --> 00:01:56,320
I forgot about that.

29
00:01:57,287 --> 00:01:59,222
Then it's settled.

30
00:02:00,290 --> 00:02:03,093
So you'll review the sourcing issue again?

31
00:02:03,093 --> 00:02:04,227
Of course.

32
00:02:04,227 --> 00:02:06,997
You'll do anything for
Mat Story's napa cabbage, right?

33
00:02:07,264 --> 00:02:08,198
Of course, sir.

34
00:02:08,532 --> 00:02:11,702
I've spent over 20 years
researching napa cabbage at Mat Story.

35
00:02:12,202 --> 00:02:15,539
I'll do whatever it takes
to solve this sourcing issue.

36
00:02:15,539 --> 00:02:17,574
The napa cabbage
that you've been dreaming of...

37
00:02:18,041 --> 00:02:18,875
I...

38
00:02:19,476 --> 00:02:22,079
I'll make sure you get it.

39
00:02:22,079 --> 00:02:23,880
Then this time,

40
00:02:24,481 --> 00:02:25,749
please make sure you solve it.

41
00:02:28,352 --> 00:02:29,319
Please work hard on it.

42
00:02:32,255 --> 00:02:33,256
Work hard?

43
00:02:36,493 --> 00:02:38,028
You're the one who'll be doing
all the hard work.

44
00:02:40,397 --> 00:02:41,264
The real...

45
00:02:43,166 --> 00:02:44,468
hard work.

46
00:03:17,067 --> 00:03:21,138
(Jeongseong Kimchi, Baekseonjang Kimchi)

47
00:03:34,685 --> 00:03:36,954
I miss you, Daddy.

48
00:03:37,621 --> 00:03:40,157
You worked very hard today, honey.

49
00:03:43,026 --> 00:03:46,196
It must be morning
in Toronto right now, right?

50
00:04:12,089 --> 00:04:14,691
(Mat Story)

51
00:04:20,931 --> 00:04:21,765
My goodness.

52
00:04:23,400 --> 00:04:24,568
Look at the HR announcement.

53
00:04:26,370 --> 00:04:27,337
Next Monday?

54
00:04:28,071 --> 00:04:29,606
Wow. That's really sudden.

55
00:04:30,173 --> 00:04:32,109
This is what happens
when you don't have connections.

56
00:04:33,010 --> 00:04:35,045
So where is this Yeonri-ri branch?

57
00:04:35,679 --> 00:04:37,014
Don't you know?

58
00:04:37,014 --> 00:04:39,950
They call it a branch,
but it's basically exile.

59
00:04:44,588 --> 00:04:46,290
I'll be getting off here.

60
00:04:46,290 --> 00:04:47,157
Sure.

61
00:04:49,359 --> 00:04:51,361
- I'm sorry.
- I'm sorry.

62
00:04:52,696 --> 00:04:53,897
Sure. Be sorry.

63
00:05:31,568 --> 00:05:33,337
(Seong Tae Hun
New Business Department Manager)

64
00:05:33,337 --> 00:05:34,738
(Transfer Order to Yeonri-ri)

65
00:05:49,553 --> 00:05:52,456
(Director's Office)

66
00:06:10,073 --> 00:06:11,842
Let's not just talk about golf.

67
00:06:23,520 --> 00:06:24,688
Mr. Seong.

68
00:06:24,688 --> 00:06:26,723
I was just about to call you in
to congratulate you.

69
00:06:28,458 --> 00:06:29,359
Mr. Choi.

70
00:06:29,559 --> 00:06:31,028
Members of the board.

71
00:06:31,862 --> 00:06:34,965
This is the man leading
the napa cabbage revolution.

72
00:06:35,499 --> 00:06:38,669
Manager Seong Tae Hun
of the Yeonri-ri Branch.

73
00:06:39,670 --> 00:06:41,571
Let me tell you about this man.

74
00:06:41,571 --> 00:06:43,907
"I will do anything for the company."

75
00:06:43,907 --> 00:06:45,142
Thanks to him,

76
00:06:45,142 --> 00:06:47,311
and his willingness
to work hard for Mat Story,

77
00:06:49,479 --> 00:06:51,281
I was able to make
this wonderful decision today.

78
00:06:52,282 --> 00:06:53,317
Everyone.

79
00:06:53,317 --> 00:06:56,420
Please give a round of applause
for Mr. Seong.

80
00:07:01,725 --> 00:07:04,094
He's factory staff now?

81
00:07:04,094 --> 00:07:05,028
Sounds great.

82
00:07:05,028 --> 00:07:06,463
Mr. Choi.

83
00:07:07,965 --> 00:07:10,367
Could I speak with you?

84
00:07:12,135 --> 00:07:13,270
What is it, Mr. Seong?

85
00:07:13,537 --> 00:07:14,972
Is there a problem?

86
00:07:15,973 --> 00:07:18,909
Mr. Choi. Yeonri-ri?

87
00:07:18,909 --> 00:07:20,010
This...

88
00:07:20,410 --> 00:07:21,945
isn't right.

89
00:07:22,446 --> 00:07:24,514
Isn't this what you wanted?

90
00:07:25,048 --> 00:07:26,650
You said napa cabbage was important.

91
00:07:27,084 --> 00:07:29,853
If the inconsistent suppliers
are the problem,

92
00:07:30,153 --> 00:07:31,455
then we should just...

93
00:07:31,455 --> 00:07:34,925
create our own exclusive source
to ensure consistency.

94
00:07:34,925 --> 00:07:35,959
But...

95
00:07:36,493 --> 00:07:38,228
Mr. Choi.

96
00:07:38,228 --> 00:07:40,163
You're not sending me to Gyeonggi-do
where there's a smart farm.

97
00:07:40,163 --> 00:07:42,966
You're sending me to Yeonri-ri,
where there isn't even a research team.

98
00:07:44,034 --> 00:07:46,370
I know what that means.

99
00:07:49,406 --> 00:07:51,308
Come on. If you know...

100
00:07:52,376 --> 00:07:53,443
Pardon?

101
00:07:53,443 --> 00:07:55,846
The company needs you there.

102
00:07:55,846 --> 00:07:57,247
Are you refusing to go?

103
00:08:00,584 --> 00:08:01,918
Are you going to resign?

104
00:08:03,787 --> 00:08:04,588
I...

105
00:08:05,689 --> 00:08:06,623
I...

106
00:08:08,325 --> 00:08:10,160
I'm giving you a great opportunity here.

107
00:08:11,561 --> 00:08:12,929
Whether you take it,

108
00:08:13,830 --> 00:08:15,532
or not...

109
00:08:16,833 --> 00:08:18,268
That's up to you.

110
00:08:19,503 --> 00:08:20,337
But...

111
00:08:20,871 --> 00:08:21,738
Sir...

112
00:08:45,696 --> 00:08:49,333
(Resignation Letter)

113
00:09:15,459 --> 00:09:16,493
Ji Cheon...

114
00:09:18,028 --> 00:09:20,397
He has to finish med school
and open a clinic.

115
00:09:22,099 --> 00:09:24,101
Ji Sang and Ji Gu in Toronto...

116
00:09:25,402 --> 00:09:26,803
still have to finish their studies.

117
00:09:30,340 --> 00:09:31,842
And you still call yourself
the head of this family?

118
00:09:35,545 --> 00:09:36,813
Did you even think about us?

119
00:09:36,813 --> 00:09:39,182
Do you want us all to end up
on the street?

120
00:09:41,985 --> 00:09:43,086
What have I done?

121
00:10:01,038 --> 00:10:01,872
What?

122
00:10:03,340 --> 00:10:04,441
It's okay.

123
00:10:33,937 --> 00:10:34,771
Yes.

124
00:10:35,472 --> 00:10:37,341
I gave my 20 years to Mat Story.

125
00:10:38,976 --> 00:10:40,544
Even if I hate it, I'll do it again.

126
00:10:42,479 --> 00:10:45,215
I, Seong Tae Hun, won't go down like this.

127
00:10:48,986 --> 00:10:55,192
(EP 1 - Was I Meant to Become a Farmer?)

128
00:11:14,044 --> 00:11:15,712
What am I doing here?

129
00:11:15,712 --> 00:11:16,747
What came over me?

130
00:11:16,747 --> 00:11:18,615
Have I lost my mind?

131
00:11:18,615 --> 00:11:20,150
Why did I say something
I didn't have to say?

132
00:11:20,150 --> 00:11:22,519
You idiot.

133
00:11:25,188 --> 00:11:26,189
Wait a minute.

134
00:11:26,957 --> 00:11:28,992
Isn't this what you wanted?

135
00:11:29,660 --> 00:11:31,228
You said napa cabbage was important.

136
00:11:33,530 --> 00:11:34,698
Wait a minute. Stop.

137
00:11:35,732 --> 00:11:37,734
Then I'll just prove it.

138
00:11:37,935 --> 00:11:39,136
Seong Tae Hun napa cabbage.

139
00:11:39,136 --> 00:11:41,438
Wasn't I going to do this before
retiring anyway?

140
00:11:49,413 --> 00:11:51,982
(Mat Story Yeonri-ri Branch)

141
00:11:52,149 --> 00:11:53,984
This place is a dump. Darn it.

142
00:12:23,981 --> 00:12:25,816
Napa cabbage and people have
something in common.

143
00:12:26,650 --> 00:12:27,784
There are people that you just know...

144
00:12:27,784 --> 00:12:31,722
you shouldn't mess with.

145
00:12:31,722 --> 00:12:33,023
the moment you meet them.

146
00:12:34,091 --> 00:12:35,559
(Yeonri-ri)

147
00:12:39,529 --> 00:12:41,131
A crime-free village.

148
00:12:41,531 --> 00:12:43,033
This is Yeonri-ri.

149
00:12:44,001 --> 00:12:45,002
Welcome.

150
00:12:53,343 --> 00:12:54,444
Are you from Seoul?

151
00:12:54,978 --> 00:12:56,680
What are you doing here on this hot day?

152
00:12:57,481 --> 00:13:00,284
Oh. I'm from Mat Story.

153
00:13:01,385 --> 00:13:02,419
Mat Story?

154
00:13:04,087 --> 00:13:05,455
What's this now?

155
00:13:05,889 --> 00:13:06,723
Pardon?

156
00:13:07,190 --> 00:13:08,425
You got transferred here?

157
00:13:08,892 --> 00:13:09,826
Yes.

158
00:13:10,160 --> 00:13:12,362
Are you a resident here?

159
00:13:12,362 --> 00:13:13,497
I'm the village chief here.

160
00:13:14,965 --> 00:13:16,266
The village chief.

161
00:13:16,833 --> 00:13:19,202
I'm looking for a place to stay nearby.

162
00:13:19,202 --> 00:13:20,938
Which real estate office should I go to?

163
00:13:23,573 --> 00:13:25,976
You're incredibly lucky...

164
00:13:25,976 --> 00:13:28,312
to have run into me at the perfect time.

165
00:13:28,812 --> 00:13:30,914
Nothing works in this village without me.

166
00:13:30,914 --> 00:13:32,449
(Yeonri-ri)

167
00:13:32,449 --> 00:13:35,686
I'm moving here by myself,
so I don't need a big place.

168
00:13:36,320 --> 00:13:38,121
Your wife must be thrilled.

169
00:13:38,121 --> 00:13:39,957
Seeing each other only on weekends
is a blessing, right?

170
00:13:41,425 --> 00:13:44,361
My wife and kids are overseas.

171
00:13:44,361 --> 00:13:46,663
You're a free bird.

172
00:13:46,663 --> 00:13:48,732
You flew and ended up here?

173
00:13:49,900 --> 00:13:51,001
Yeah.

174
00:13:51,001 --> 00:13:53,804
I guess you are taking a break
for a little bit.

175
00:13:53,804 --> 00:13:54,871
Who knows?

176
00:13:55,672 --> 00:13:57,407
You might go back up to Seoul soon.

177
00:13:58,508 --> 00:13:59,610
Would you like to start with that house?

178
00:14:07,517 --> 00:14:09,453
You don't see yards like this
in Seoul, right?

179
00:14:10,187 --> 00:14:12,456
Are you sure this is a yard?

180
00:14:12,956 --> 00:14:14,091
This house is...

181
00:14:14,091 --> 00:14:14,992
No thanks.

182
00:14:19,429 --> 00:14:21,264
I don't think you can call this a house.

183
00:14:23,033 --> 00:14:25,702
These days, everything is full option.
Did you look thoroughly?

184
00:14:26,737 --> 00:14:29,239
Yes, full option.
But it's more like negative features?

185
00:14:30,407 --> 00:14:31,541
Are you sure you came to live here?

186
00:14:32,242 --> 00:14:33,443
Maybe you didn't come to live here.

187
00:14:36,513 --> 00:14:38,749
This house has
the highest ceiling in Yeonri-ri.

188
00:14:38,749 --> 00:14:40,984
Yes, according to your standards.

189
00:14:40,984 --> 00:14:41,918
My standards?

190
00:14:43,553 --> 00:14:44,488
You're tall.

191
00:14:45,122 --> 00:14:48,025
It's so hot.
How long are you going to keep looking?

192
00:14:48,025 --> 00:14:48,859
It's nice and clean, right?

193
00:14:53,964 --> 00:14:55,866
Those chickens are a bonus.

194
00:14:56,767 --> 00:14:58,835
I'm not eating chicken starting today.

195
00:15:03,807 --> 00:15:04,808
This is the last house.

196
00:15:04,808 --> 00:15:06,743
They're all in about the same condition.

197
00:15:07,477 --> 00:15:10,180
But this is the best one so far.

198
00:15:10,180 --> 00:15:12,716
Can we sign a contract today?

199
00:15:12,716 --> 00:15:14,217
I'll ask.

200
00:15:19,356 --> 00:15:20,991
He likes Man Sik's place.

201
00:15:20,991 --> 00:15:22,059
This is the best one so far.

202
00:15:22,059 --> 00:15:22,893
What?

203
00:15:23,593 --> 00:15:25,429
- Really? All right.
- There's no time.

204
00:15:25,963 --> 00:15:27,664
Gosh. I'm sorry.

205
00:15:27,664 --> 00:15:29,666
There's a lien on the house,

206
00:15:29,666 --> 00:15:31,068
so it can't be rented.

207
00:15:31,702 --> 00:15:34,438
It looks like someone
caused trouble again.

208
00:15:34,438 --> 00:15:36,473
I have an appointment today
that I must get to.

209
00:15:36,473 --> 00:15:37,207
Then...

210
00:15:38,041 --> 00:15:40,577
what about this house?

211
00:15:40,577 --> 00:15:41,812
Yes, that one is available.

212
00:15:41,812 --> 00:15:44,014
I need to get back now.

213
00:15:44,014 --> 00:15:44,982
Get going.

214
00:15:44,982 --> 00:15:46,683
- Thank you. Thank you.
- Good-bye.

215
00:15:46,683 --> 00:15:48,251
- You know the way out?
- Yes.

216
00:15:49,252 --> 00:15:51,655
Look at him go.

217
00:15:52,556 --> 00:15:53,657
Mat Story?

218
00:15:54,691 --> 00:15:56,259
Goodness. It's so hot.

219
00:16:06,169 --> 00:16:08,272
If the executive director wants to see me,

220
00:16:09,439 --> 00:16:10,941
that means it's not over yet.

221
00:16:12,175 --> 00:16:13,110
Let's tough it out.

222
00:16:13,877 --> 00:16:16,146
Even if I have to grind myself down
like cabbage filling.

223
00:16:16,947 --> 00:16:18,282
You can do it, Seong Tae Hun.

224
00:16:23,754 --> 00:16:24,688
Come in.

225
00:16:31,395 --> 00:16:32,629
Did you want to see me?

226
00:16:36,433 --> 00:16:38,869
About the Yeonri-ri transfer...

227
00:16:38,869 --> 00:16:41,805
I know that people are gossiping.

228
00:16:43,674 --> 00:16:46,310
"They sent him to a dead-end post
because he's without connections."

229
00:16:46,310 --> 00:16:48,211
"It's a trick to push him out."

230
00:16:50,013 --> 00:16:51,415
Is that what you think, too?

231
00:16:52,282 --> 00:16:54,051
Sir.

232
00:16:54,051 --> 00:16:57,187
Please reconsider the Yeonri-ri transfer.

233
00:16:58,088 --> 00:16:58,956
Yes?

234
00:17:01,091 --> 00:17:02,459
Not at all, sir.

235
00:17:03,193 --> 00:17:05,862
I already found a place
to stay in Yeonri-ri today.

236
00:17:06,763 --> 00:17:08,398
Good. That's the attitude.

237
00:17:10,634 --> 00:17:12,669
So you have three kids?

238
00:17:12,669 --> 00:17:14,404
Two are studying in Canada,

239
00:17:14,404 --> 00:17:15,839
and your eldest is in medical school?

240
00:17:17,007 --> 00:17:18,775
It must be costing you a fortune.

241
00:17:19,843 --> 00:17:21,878
How did you know?

242
00:17:23,880 --> 00:17:26,917
All fathers in Korea live the same life.

243
00:17:29,586 --> 00:17:31,321
What you'll be doing in Yeonri-ri...

244
00:17:31,321 --> 00:17:33,924
is much bigger than you think.

245
00:17:35,192 --> 00:17:37,628
It's a mission that the future of
Mat Story depends on.

246
00:17:38,629 --> 00:17:42,032
So if I successfully grow
Mat Story napa cabbage,

247
00:17:42,032 --> 00:17:44,234
does that mean I can return
to headquarters?

248
00:17:46,169 --> 00:17:47,271
Mr. Seong Tae Hun.

249
00:17:48,872 --> 00:17:49,973
Go to Yeonri-ri,

250
00:17:50,907 --> 00:17:52,909
and prove your value.

251
00:17:54,978 --> 00:17:55,912
Yes, sir.

252
00:18:06,623 --> 00:18:07,557
I...

253
00:18:08,592 --> 00:18:10,327
will make a comeback to Seoul.

254
00:18:11,528 --> 00:18:13,196
Right in the middle of this building,

255
00:18:13,196 --> 00:18:14,865
I'll put up a napa cabbage statue,

256
00:18:15,899 --> 00:18:16,733
and my kids,

257
00:18:18,001 --> 00:18:19,002
and my wife...

258
00:18:20,103 --> 00:18:22,739
will applaud me as I retire.

259
00:18:22,739 --> 00:18:24,875
I will do it.

260
00:18:52,035 --> 00:18:53,136
(Wife)

261
00:18:57,274 --> 00:18:59,176
Honey.

262
00:19:00,010 --> 00:19:01,011
Well...

263
00:19:01,778 --> 00:19:03,146
Honey.

264
00:19:03,146 --> 00:19:05,682
I was just about to call you.

265
00:19:05,682 --> 00:19:07,384
Where are you right now?

266
00:19:07,851 --> 00:19:09,219
The call keeps dropping.

267
00:19:10,187 --> 00:19:11,722
Well, you see...

268
00:19:12,389 --> 00:19:15,092
I have something to tell you.

269
00:19:15,092 --> 00:19:18,161
You do? I have something to tell you, too.

270
00:19:18,862 --> 00:19:20,497
- Oh.
- Door opening.

271
00:19:20,497 --> 00:19:21,398
By the way...

272
00:19:22,432 --> 00:19:25,269
Where are you, honey? What?

273
00:19:27,337 --> 00:19:30,607
Honey, where are you?

274
00:19:30,607 --> 00:19:31,441
Well...

275
00:19:36,380 --> 00:19:38,148
What are you doing here, honey?

276
00:19:38,148 --> 00:19:39,616
You see...

277
00:19:39,616 --> 00:19:41,752
It just happened, honey.

278
00:19:46,957 --> 00:19:47,858
Dad.

279
00:19:50,360 --> 00:19:51,962
You've grown so much.

280
00:19:52,629 --> 00:19:54,598
Dad, what's with all these boxes?

281
00:19:56,466 --> 00:19:57,301
Well...

282
00:19:59,369 --> 00:20:01,438
Are you going somewhere?

283
00:20:06,209 --> 00:20:07,511
Have you lost your mind?

284
00:20:08,111 --> 00:20:09,413
A research assignment?

285
00:20:09,746 --> 00:20:11,281
And in the countryside?

286
00:20:11,281 --> 00:20:13,450
Why didn't you tell me this sooner?

287
00:20:13,450 --> 00:20:14,785
You're the one to talk.

288
00:20:14,785 --> 00:20:17,688
What are you doing here with
the kids without telling me?

289
00:20:17,688 --> 00:20:19,423
I had my reasons.

290
00:20:19,423 --> 00:20:21,391
Exactly. Why are the kids...

291
00:20:22,025 --> 00:20:23,460
Ji Cheon. What are you doing here?

292
00:20:24,328 --> 00:20:25,729
Mom told me to come.

293
00:20:26,296 --> 00:20:28,231
I asked him to come to the airport.

294
00:20:28,231 --> 00:20:29,700
We had a lot of luggage.

295
00:20:29,700 --> 00:20:31,335
Exactly. So why?

296
00:20:34,571 --> 00:20:35,439
Ji Sang...

297
00:20:36,406 --> 00:20:37,574
was expelled.

298
00:20:37,574 --> 00:20:38,709
What?

299
00:20:39,276 --> 00:20:41,111
Expelled?

300
00:20:41,111 --> 00:20:42,846
There was a fight among some kids...

301
00:20:42,846 --> 00:20:44,748
It just happened.

302
00:20:44,748 --> 00:20:46,116
Would you understand even if I told you?

303
00:20:46,116 --> 00:20:47,784
What kind of fight was it
that you got expelled?

304
00:20:47,784 --> 00:20:50,153
Seong Ji Sang. Come here right now!

305
00:20:50,153 --> 00:20:51,555
You can scold him later.

306
00:20:51,555 --> 00:20:54,291
Right now, you need to
figure out this situation.

307
00:20:54,291 --> 00:20:57,260
You should've told me first
if something like this happened.

308
00:20:57,260 --> 00:20:59,496
Did you ever answer your phone
when I called you?

309
00:20:59,496 --> 00:21:01,832
When I called you back,
you never answered either.

310
00:21:01,832 --> 00:21:04,835
I was trying to sort things out.
That's why.

311
00:21:08,772 --> 00:21:11,041
(Moving Company)

312
00:21:16,113 --> 00:21:17,814
For now, let's go.

313
00:21:21,518 --> 00:21:23,353
Where exactly are we going?

314
00:21:27,958 --> 00:21:30,961
We'll be there in the blink of an eye.

315
00:21:31,862 --> 00:21:33,130
It's not too far from Seoul.

316
00:21:37,267 --> 00:21:40,570
(Simwoo-myeon 157 km)

317
00:21:55,485 --> 00:21:56,753
(Moving Day)

318
00:21:58,889 --> 00:21:59,890
What?

319
00:22:00,857 --> 00:22:01,758
What?

320
00:22:03,427 --> 00:22:05,162
A rural vacation?

321
00:22:06,830 --> 00:22:08,332
A rural vacation?

322
00:22:08,332 --> 00:22:09,900
This isn't the house.

323
00:22:09,900 --> 00:22:11,234
I clearly...

324
00:22:11,234 --> 00:22:13,203
showed him the pictures...

325
00:22:13,203 --> 00:22:16,473
You rented a house
just by looking at pictures?

326
00:22:16,473 --> 00:22:20,110
That's not it.
I think there's been a mistake.

327
00:22:20,110 --> 00:22:21,545
What the...

328
00:22:22,112 --> 00:22:23,046
Daddy.

329
00:22:23,046 --> 00:22:24,214
Dad.

330
00:22:24,781 --> 00:22:26,083
No one can live here.

331
00:22:26,717 --> 00:22:28,952
Look. It's haunted.

332
00:22:29,886 --> 00:22:31,254
Haunted?

333
00:22:31,688 --> 00:22:32,823
Seriously?

334
00:22:33,323 --> 00:22:34,891
No, Ji Gu. This...

335
00:22:34,891 --> 00:22:35,959
Unbelievable.

336
00:22:37,227 --> 00:22:40,530
I clearly asked for this house.

337
00:22:40,530 --> 00:22:41,999
This one.

338
00:22:42,599 --> 00:22:44,635
- It's not that.
- Stop.

339
00:22:44,635 --> 00:22:45,769
You're here.

340
00:22:46,637 --> 00:22:48,372
I thought you were coming alone,
but the whole family is here.

341
00:22:49,139 --> 00:22:50,540
- Welcome to Yeonri-ri... What?
- Chief.

342
00:22:52,376 --> 00:22:53,543
This isn't the house.

343
00:22:54,144 --> 00:22:55,112
What's wrong?

344
00:22:55,379 --> 00:22:57,247
Well, I...

345
00:22:57,814 --> 00:22:59,983
I was talking about this house.

346
00:23:00,684 --> 00:23:01,885
We looked at so many houses.

347
00:23:01,885 --> 00:23:03,153
How would I know which house is which?

348
00:23:05,289 --> 00:23:07,624
It's so hot.
How long are you going to keep looking?

349
00:23:07,624 --> 00:23:09,393
You can take a look.
I won't do it anymore.

350
00:23:09,726 --> 00:23:10,994
I won't do it. I won't.

351
00:23:11,928 --> 00:23:13,397
What about this house?

352
00:23:14,064 --> 00:23:15,165
Yes, that one is available.

353
00:23:29,212 --> 00:23:30,714
They just got here from Canada.

354
00:23:30,714 --> 00:23:32,649
How can they live in a place like this?

355
00:23:33,183 --> 00:23:34,718
Actually, it's perfect.

356
00:23:34,718 --> 00:23:36,486
That other house has
a broken water pipe right now.

357
00:23:36,486 --> 00:23:38,188
There's no hot water either.

358
00:23:38,188 --> 00:23:39,256
This is what we'll do.

359
00:23:39,623 --> 00:23:40,791
You stay here for now.

360
00:23:40,791 --> 00:23:42,793
When the repairs are done,
you can move there, okay?

361
00:23:44,361 --> 00:23:47,264
This place is closer to
the Mat Story field anyway.

362
00:23:52,903 --> 00:23:53,904
Sir.

363
00:23:54,504 --> 00:23:56,707
Should we unload your stuff or not?

364
00:23:56,707 --> 00:23:57,941
It's getting dark.

365
00:23:59,509 --> 00:24:01,311
Are you going to make your family...

366
00:24:01,311 --> 00:24:03,413
sleep in the yard tonight? Well?

367
00:24:15,359 --> 00:24:16,493
Please unload everything.

368
00:24:16,493 --> 00:24:17,427
He said to unload.

369
00:24:25,269 --> 00:24:28,272
I'm sure the inside is okay.

370
00:24:31,375 --> 00:24:32,309
Let's go, Ji Sang.

371
00:24:45,856 --> 00:24:46,923
Be careful.

372
00:24:49,993 --> 00:24:50,927
Ugh, dust.

373
00:24:58,902 --> 00:25:00,437
Be careful, Ji Gu. Be careful.

374
00:25:00,437 --> 00:25:02,205
Don't run. Don't run. It's dusty.

375
00:25:02,439 --> 00:25:03,774
No.

376
00:25:04,441 --> 00:25:05,475
No. Bugs! Bugs!

377
00:25:05,475 --> 00:25:07,044
I'm going back.
I'm going back to Seoul.

378
00:25:07,044 --> 00:25:08,211
No, no, no.

379
00:25:08,211 --> 00:25:09,780
It's dangerous right now. It's nighttime.

380
00:25:09,780 --> 00:25:11,882
I can clean this place up quickly.
I'll get rid of the cockroaches and...

381
00:25:11,882 --> 00:25:12,849
Bugs.

382
00:25:14,351 --> 00:25:16,386
A spider over there.

383
00:25:19,589 --> 00:25:21,091
You're not supposed to kill spiders.

384
00:25:21,692 --> 00:25:22,626
They say it brings bad luck.

385
00:25:25,896 --> 00:25:28,332
Get lost. This is my room.

386
00:25:28,332 --> 00:25:30,033
No, that's mine.

387
00:25:30,634 --> 00:25:31,535
Mom.

388
00:25:31,535 --> 00:25:34,071
Be quiet. I'm exhausted.

389
00:25:35,138 --> 00:25:36,640
I can't share a room with him.

390
00:25:36,640 --> 00:25:37,908
I need my own room.

391
00:25:38,275 --> 00:25:40,777
Me too. He's so dirty.

392
00:25:40,777 --> 00:25:42,045
He's always dropping snack crumbs.

393
00:25:43,814 --> 00:25:45,082
You two. Come here.

394
00:25:45,749 --> 00:25:46,717
Right now.

395
00:25:47,250 --> 00:25:48,218
Come here.

396
00:25:50,087 --> 00:25:51,421
That's not fair.

397
00:25:51,688 --> 00:25:53,423
I want my own room!

398
00:25:53,423 --> 00:25:54,358
As for the room...

399
00:25:57,661 --> 00:25:59,963
You have to share a room.
If you don't want to...

400
00:26:02,866 --> 00:26:03,734
Get out.

401
00:26:05,269 --> 00:26:06,370
Dad.

402
00:26:06,737 --> 00:26:09,539
Is your company bankrupt?

403
00:26:11,275 --> 00:26:12,509
No.

404
00:26:12,743 --> 00:26:14,411
I came here to do research.

405
00:26:14,411 --> 00:26:16,313
Development. Yes.

406
00:26:16,980 --> 00:26:17,948
Development.

407
00:26:19,049 --> 00:26:19,983
My head.

408
00:26:29,860 --> 00:26:30,827
Honey.

409
00:26:31,461 --> 00:26:32,863
Be careful. Are you okay?

410
00:26:33,864 --> 00:26:34,898
Goodness.

411
00:26:35,699 --> 00:26:36,733
A little more.

412
00:26:36,733 --> 00:26:38,235
No. Push. Push.

413
00:26:38,735 --> 00:26:40,804
No, Ji Cheon. Pull it that way.

414
00:26:40,804 --> 00:26:41,738
Push.

415
00:26:41,738 --> 00:26:43,173
Don't push like that. Grab the top.

416
00:26:43,173 --> 00:26:45,008
Grab the top. Grab the top.

417
00:26:45,676 --> 00:26:48,545
You have to grab the top.

418
00:26:50,213 --> 00:26:51,348
I'm sorry, but can you please help?

419
00:26:51,982 --> 00:26:54,251
You don't have much stuff.
It'll be done soon.

420
00:26:54,251 --> 00:26:55,752
You can't see anything once the sun sets.

421
00:26:55,752 --> 00:26:57,287
Finish it up quickly. Come on.

422
00:26:58,622 --> 00:26:59,556
Finish it up.

423
00:27:01,792 --> 00:27:03,360
He's no help.

424
00:27:04,227 --> 00:27:05,595
Slowly. Slowly. Slowly.

425
00:27:12,369 --> 00:27:13,637
No.

426
00:27:14,171 --> 00:27:17,074
Are you moving your stuff or
breaking the cart?

427
00:27:18,075 --> 00:27:19,910
The first one, obviously.

428
00:27:21,244 --> 00:27:22,312
Keep up the good work.

429
00:27:26,717 --> 00:27:28,285
- Thank you.
- Bye.

430
00:27:29,987 --> 00:27:32,322
It won't be delivered tomorrow.
I'm going crazy here.

431
00:27:32,322 --> 00:27:34,157
Even in Canada, everything gets delivered.

432
00:27:34,157 --> 00:27:36,059
How am I supposed to live here?

433
00:27:38,562 --> 00:27:40,731
Was this always this big?

434
00:27:41,298 --> 00:27:42,132
It...

435
00:27:42,132 --> 00:27:45,636
By the way, the gas isn't connected.

436
00:27:45,636 --> 00:27:47,404
Isn't the landlord coming? Where is he?

437
00:27:48,038 --> 00:27:50,474
- Well...
- Here's the landlady.

438
00:27:56,546 --> 00:27:58,482
(Deok Rae)

439
00:28:03,053 --> 00:28:04,955
(Ok Rae)

440
00:28:07,557 --> 00:28:09,526
(Mak Rae)

441
00:28:15,966 --> 00:28:19,202
Is this a dining table
or a wooden platform?

442
00:28:19,202 --> 00:28:21,305
Why is it so big?

443
00:28:21,305 --> 00:28:24,141
The furniture doesn't match at all.

444
00:28:24,141 --> 00:28:26,109
How chaotic.

445
00:28:26,109 --> 00:28:27,711
Are you the landlady?

446
00:28:28,178 --> 00:28:30,080
I'm Seong Tae Hun, the tenant.

447
00:28:30,080 --> 00:28:31,114
Not me.

448
00:28:31,515 --> 00:28:32,382
Her.

449
00:28:34,184 --> 00:28:35,652
What about the gas?

450
00:28:35,652 --> 00:28:38,355
You need to call the gas company.
Why are you looking for me?

451
00:28:38,355 --> 00:28:39,556
Do you want me to fart instead?

452
00:28:39,556 --> 00:28:42,192
Stop it, Ok Rae.

453
00:28:42,659 --> 00:28:45,028
You need LPG.

454
00:28:45,028 --> 00:28:46,563
Take out your phone.

455
00:28:47,064 --> 00:28:50,100
This is the number you should call.

456
00:28:51,368 --> 00:28:53,270
- Okay?
- Okay.

457
00:28:53,270 --> 00:28:55,439
We came by to see how you were doing.

458
00:28:55,772 --> 00:28:58,375
The whole family is here.

459
00:28:58,375 --> 00:28:59,576
It's nice and lively.

460
00:28:59,743 --> 00:29:00,844
Welcome.

461
00:29:01,211 --> 00:29:02,913
Do you want me to fart for you?

462
00:29:02,913 --> 00:29:04,615
Ok Rae. Let's go. Let's go.

463
00:29:11,288 --> 00:29:14,291
(Moving Day)

464
00:29:38,715 --> 00:29:40,817
I'll be washing the rice until tomorrow.

465
00:29:42,319 --> 00:29:44,521
How am I supposed to cook
in a place like this?

466
00:29:48,458 --> 00:29:49,660
Should we eat out today?

467
00:29:49,660 --> 00:29:51,295
We must eat jajangmyeon on moving day.

468
00:29:51,295 --> 00:29:53,864
Ji Sang. Ji Gu. It's been a while
since you had jajangmyeon, right?

469
00:29:53,864 --> 00:29:54,765
Let's go.

470
00:29:58,835 --> 00:29:59,970
This is jajangmyeon?

471
00:30:02,406 --> 00:30:04,942
It's cooler now that the wind is blowing.

472
00:30:07,010 --> 00:30:07,945
It's good.

473
00:30:09,012 --> 00:30:10,881
Let's eat something even better soon.

474
00:30:11,315 --> 00:30:12,849
There's no restaurant that delivers here.

475
00:30:12,849 --> 00:30:15,652
I don't know
if we're eating kimchi for the ramyeon,

476
00:30:16,153 --> 00:30:18,822
or the other way around.

477
00:30:19,856 --> 00:30:21,625
It's good when you eat them
together, honey.

478
00:30:22,459 --> 00:30:24,361
With this,

479
00:30:27,130 --> 00:30:28,832
that kimchi goes really well.

480
00:31:06,603 --> 00:31:07,904
Where am I?

481
00:31:07,904 --> 00:31:09,239
I'll only stay for a few days.

482
00:31:10,240 --> 00:31:12,276
When did you get here, honey?

483
00:31:12,276 --> 00:31:15,345
If I left you alone
after seeing this mess,

484
00:31:15,345 --> 00:31:16,913
I wouldn't be able to sleep. That's why.

485
00:31:21,218 --> 00:31:23,487
Mom. Mom!

486
00:31:23,487 --> 00:31:25,055
- What is it? What?
- A centipede.

487
00:31:25,055 --> 00:31:26,556
Wow. A centipede. It's so gross.

488
00:31:26,556 --> 00:31:28,625
- A centipede.
- A centipede.

489
00:31:28,625 --> 00:31:30,093
It's so disgusting.

490
00:31:30,093 --> 00:31:31,094
A centipede?

491
00:31:31,428 --> 00:31:33,930
Ji Sang. Go get Ji Cheon,

492
00:31:33,930 --> 00:31:35,432
and close the door behind you.

493
00:31:35,432 --> 00:31:38,468
No. You go close it.

494
00:31:38,869 --> 00:31:40,737
Go now. Go.

495
00:31:40,737 --> 00:31:42,940
Go close the door now.

496
00:31:43,573 --> 00:31:44,942
But it's so gross.

497
00:31:52,683 --> 00:31:54,851
I think my whole body is itchy.

498
00:31:56,053 --> 00:31:58,455
Maybe we should just sleep here
for tonight.

499
00:32:02,592 --> 00:32:03,627
Dad.

500
00:32:03,627 --> 00:32:05,629
- Yes?
- Wake up.

501
00:32:12,336 --> 00:32:13,837
Mom.

502
00:32:13,837 --> 00:32:14,738
Yes?

503
00:32:14,738 --> 00:32:16,206
I'm scared.

504
00:32:16,206 --> 00:32:18,141
Ji Gu, you're scared?

505
00:32:18,141 --> 00:32:20,744
I'm scared because all the lights are off.

506
00:32:21,912 --> 00:32:23,580
It kind of feels like we're camping.

507
00:32:25,015 --> 00:32:25,983
Actually,

508
00:32:26,883 --> 00:32:29,620
they say the countryside is much better
for people than the city.

509
00:32:30,621 --> 00:32:31,888
There's phytoncide from the trees,

510
00:32:32,522 --> 00:32:34,658
the smell of grass calms your nerves,

511
00:32:35,459 --> 00:32:37,060
and since there's no noise pollution,

512
00:32:37,060 --> 00:32:39,663
your body produces more melatonin
so you can sleep deeper.

513
00:32:40,731 --> 00:32:43,066
Yes, but...

514
00:32:43,834 --> 00:32:46,837
we should sleep at night, right?

515
00:32:47,471 --> 00:32:48,405
Okay.

516
00:32:48,405 --> 00:32:49,473
But I'm scared.

517
00:32:49,473 --> 00:32:50,974
Let's just hang in there a little longer.

518
00:32:50,974 --> 00:32:52,409
But I don't want to.

519
00:32:52,409 --> 00:32:53,310
Good night.

520
00:32:53,310 --> 00:32:54,411
Oh, my God.

521
00:32:55,312 --> 00:32:56,813
I can't sleep.

522
00:32:58,081 --> 00:32:59,449
I'll be up all night.

523
00:33:17,200 --> 00:33:18,302
You three.

524
00:33:19,870 --> 00:33:21,038
You've all grown so much.

525
00:34:55,299 --> 00:34:57,701
Why doesn't this key go in?

526
00:34:59,736 --> 00:35:00,637
Darn.

527
00:35:01,004 --> 00:35:03,774
(Mat Story Yeonri-ri Branch)

528
00:35:38,375 --> 00:35:39,409
What are you doing?

529
00:35:39,409 --> 00:35:41,111
Who are you? Who?

530
00:35:57,260 --> 00:36:00,230
Do people in this town
enjoy scaring others?

531
00:36:00,964 --> 00:36:02,332
Since yesterday...

532
00:36:03,700 --> 00:36:04,635
It's open.

533
00:36:06,937 --> 00:36:08,005
Are you the building manager?

534
00:36:09,239 --> 00:36:10,674
Or a Mat Story employee?

535
00:36:22,586 --> 00:36:24,187
You'll be able to open most things.

536
00:36:27,057 --> 00:36:29,026
Wait. Wait...

537
00:36:31,928 --> 00:36:33,730
So you think I'm the outcast
they sent down here?

538
00:36:33,997 --> 00:36:35,632
You can look down on me all you want.

539
00:36:54,318 --> 00:36:56,954
(Napa cabbage research fully suspended)

540
00:37:11,835 --> 00:37:14,471
How am I supposed to research
napa cabbage in a place like this?

541
00:37:29,486 --> 00:37:31,922
Napa cabbage research fully suspended?

542
00:37:44,801 --> 00:37:47,537
I want to go back to Seoul.

543
00:37:47,537 --> 00:37:49,439
I'm going to kill Director Choi.

544
00:37:49,439 --> 00:37:51,208
All you Mat Story jerks.

545
00:37:54,044 --> 00:37:55,145
You abandoned me?

546
00:37:55,846 --> 00:37:56,980
Me?

547
00:38:13,463 --> 00:38:15,799
(2016 Work Log)

548
00:38:18,702 --> 00:38:20,871
The soil has been neglected
for a long time,

549
00:38:20,871 --> 00:38:24,308
so drainage and nutrients are
completely imbalanced.

550
00:38:24,308 --> 00:38:26,743
All professional staff
need to be deployed.

551
00:38:27,911 --> 00:38:29,513
The site selection was a failure.

552
00:38:33,216 --> 00:38:34,551
What's going to happen now?

553
00:38:37,821 --> 00:38:39,022
Do nothing.

554
00:38:40,624 --> 00:38:41,558
Nothing.

555
00:38:43,560 --> 00:38:45,595
Headquarters has abandoned Yeonri-ri.

556
00:38:45,595 --> 00:38:47,164
Do nothing.

557
00:38:48,398 --> 00:38:49,366
Headquarters...

558
00:38:51,234 --> 00:38:52,836
has abandoned Yeonri-ri.

559
00:39:31,275 --> 00:39:33,577
Why won't this start?

560
00:39:43,053 --> 00:39:44,288
Why won't it?

561
00:39:46,223 --> 00:39:48,458
This is his first day at work.

562
00:39:50,794 --> 00:39:51,828
It's hot.

563
00:39:53,130 --> 00:39:54,197
It's hot.

564
00:39:56,600 --> 00:39:57,901
Air conditioner...

565
00:39:59,937 --> 00:40:00,871
Come on.

566
00:40:06,610 --> 00:40:08,979
Is it jet lag? I'm dying.

567
00:40:12,416 --> 00:40:13,383
It's hot.

568
00:40:15,719 --> 00:40:19,256
If you're hot, why are you wrapped up
in a blanket?

569
00:40:19,256 --> 00:40:21,391
Goodness. Look at all this sweat.

570
00:40:21,391 --> 00:40:22,492
Goodness.

571
00:40:24,628 --> 00:40:25,462
What?

572
00:40:26,863 --> 00:40:27,898
Dr. Seong?

573
00:40:29,032 --> 00:40:30,534
Dr. Seong.

574
00:40:32,269 --> 00:40:33,337
Dr. Seong?

575
00:40:37,374 --> 00:40:43,947
(Yeonri-ri Village)

576
00:40:55,258 --> 00:40:56,226
This is nice.

577
00:42:02,359 --> 00:42:03,560
Son, where are you?

578
00:42:03,560 --> 00:42:04,795
You need to eat lunch.

579
00:42:16,440 --> 00:42:17,240
Move out of the way.

580
00:42:22,412 --> 00:42:24,648
Don't use your phone while you're walking.
Or you'll get hurt.

581
00:42:29,953 --> 00:42:31,254
I should go back now.

582
00:42:49,039 --> 00:42:51,241
What's that? Is that a snail?

583
00:42:52,009 --> 00:42:54,411
What is he doing in the rice field?

584
00:43:00,984 --> 00:43:03,587
Your clothes are dirty already.
Come with us.

585
00:43:05,789 --> 00:43:06,723
Me?

586
00:43:06,957 --> 00:43:09,393
Who else is there?

587
00:43:09,960 --> 00:43:12,996
Are we allowed to take him with us?

588
00:43:12,996 --> 00:43:15,098
He's with that Mat Story family
that caused all that fuss.

589
00:43:15,098 --> 00:43:18,201
Mat Story or whatever,
we're short on workers.

590
00:43:18,201 --> 00:43:20,704
Making a guy who's doing nothing
work won't kill him.

591
00:43:22,205 --> 00:43:23,073
Let's go.

592
00:43:25,776 --> 00:43:27,244
Together.

593
00:43:40,057 --> 00:43:41,291
It smells amazing in here.

594
00:43:41,658 --> 00:43:42,559
Hey.

595
00:43:43,460 --> 00:43:46,563
Looks like a great harvest this year.

596
00:43:46,897 --> 00:43:48,398
Look at them hanging everywhere.

597
00:43:48,398 --> 00:43:49,599
My goodness.

598
00:43:50,067 --> 00:43:53,637
These cucumbers are smooth
and handsome, just like me.

599
00:43:54,004 --> 00:43:55,238
Go on in.

600
00:44:03,046 --> 00:44:04,014
Wow.

601
00:44:06,617 --> 00:44:08,251
Close your mouth before a fly goes in.

602
00:44:08,251 --> 00:44:09,353
You've never seen a cucumber field before?

603
00:44:10,387 --> 00:44:12,689
No, I've never seen a cucumber field
like this.

604
00:44:13,457 --> 00:44:14,324
Here.

605
00:44:15,025 --> 00:44:18,795
Take this and start from over there.
Pick as you go.

606
00:44:19,663 --> 00:44:20,597
Look.

607
00:44:22,332 --> 00:44:24,167
Like this. Like this.

608
00:44:28,472 --> 00:44:30,374
If you don't fill this basket,
you won't get paid today.

609
00:44:31,375 --> 00:44:32,209
Okay.

610
00:44:33,043 --> 00:44:34,544
What? Wait.

611
00:44:34,544 --> 00:44:36,913
I've never done this kind of work before.

612
00:44:39,816 --> 00:44:42,119
You think I was born
picking cucumbers then?

613
00:44:42,119 --> 00:44:43,320
Do it before I smack you.

614
00:44:45,422 --> 00:44:46,590
I'll try.

615
00:44:57,034 --> 00:44:58,602
When am I going to organize all this?

616
00:45:01,438 --> 00:45:05,042
First, I'll put away the blankets.

617
00:45:06,843 --> 00:45:07,911
Stationery...

618
00:45:22,459 --> 00:45:23,327
There.

619
00:45:23,794 --> 00:45:24,728
Come on.

620
00:45:25,462 --> 00:45:27,564
My phone.

621
00:45:27,564 --> 00:45:29,933
I need to call Carol.

622
00:45:31,101 --> 00:45:32,369
Mom.

623
00:45:33,503 --> 00:45:36,039
We're going back to Seoul, right?

624
00:45:36,840 --> 00:45:39,276
Or let's go back to Toronto. Please?

625
00:45:39,276 --> 00:45:42,279
What would you even do in Toronto?

626
00:45:43,747 --> 00:45:45,749
Carol says she misses me.

627
00:45:47,217 --> 00:45:49,519
I even have money to buy a plane ticket.

628
00:45:50,220 --> 00:45:53,023
So let's go back.

629
00:45:53,023 --> 00:45:54,424
Is anyone home?

630
00:45:56,460 --> 00:45:58,395
Hello?

631
00:45:59,463 --> 00:46:00,464
Yes?

632
00:46:17,848 --> 00:46:18,849
Who are you?

633
00:46:19,416 --> 00:46:20,250
Hi.

634
00:46:20,817 --> 00:46:22,753
You're from Seoul, right?

635
00:46:25,522 --> 00:46:26,590
Can I help you?

636
00:46:28,925 --> 00:46:29,826
Well...

637
00:46:30,360 --> 00:46:34,131
She's the head
of the Yeonri-ri Women's Association.

638
00:46:34,464 --> 00:46:36,967
She also runs a cafe in town,

639
00:46:36,967 --> 00:46:38,468
and a hair salon.

640
00:46:40,003 --> 00:46:41,204
She's the big shot of Yeonri-ri.

641
00:46:44,141 --> 00:46:45,475
I'm not a big shot.

642
00:46:46,777 --> 00:46:48,545
I'm Nam Hye Sun.

643
00:46:49,746 --> 00:46:52,549
I live right across from you.

644
00:46:54,484 --> 00:46:55,385
I see.

645
00:46:56,019 --> 00:46:58,055
It's nice to meet you.

646
00:46:59,756 --> 00:47:02,059
So when are you planning to
go back to Seoul?

647
00:47:03,260 --> 00:47:05,729
My husband will go back
after he finishes his work.

648
00:47:06,196 --> 00:47:08,198
But I might go back sooner.

649
00:47:08,865 --> 00:47:11,535
Those people from Mat Story...

650
00:47:11,935 --> 00:47:13,637
Did they last two months?

651
00:47:13,637 --> 00:47:15,005
No.

652
00:47:15,005 --> 00:47:16,907
The longest lasted a month and a half.

653
00:47:17,441 --> 00:47:18,875
Oh.

654
00:47:20,744 --> 00:47:24,715
If you're planning to stay for
more than a year,

655
00:47:25,015 --> 00:47:26,650
you'll have to join
the Women's Association.

656
00:47:27,751 --> 00:47:28,785
I'm sorry.

657
00:47:29,419 --> 00:47:31,388
I think we'll be going back before then.

658
00:47:34,424 --> 00:47:35,859
Is that so?

659
00:47:37,194 --> 00:47:38,795
All right then.

660
00:47:39,630 --> 00:47:41,498
- Let's go.
- Let's go.

661
00:47:43,867 --> 00:47:45,369
She didn't even offer us a glass of water.

662
00:47:46,169 --> 00:47:47,337
That's just wrong.

663
00:47:47,337 --> 00:47:48,372
Forget it.

664
00:47:48,372 --> 00:47:50,374
It's not like we don't have
water to drink.

665
00:47:50,674 --> 00:47:54,544
If you say that, people will say
we're hazing her.

666
00:47:55,579 --> 00:47:56,880
This is upsetting.

667
00:48:00,117 --> 00:48:01,118
Unbelievable.

668
00:48:02,586 --> 00:48:04,755
This is real hazing.

669
00:48:20,671 --> 00:48:22,406
It doesn't look that difficult.

670
00:48:24,942 --> 00:48:26,109
Do I just pick it?

671
00:48:29,479 --> 00:48:30,347
Ow, that hurts.

672
00:48:34,618 --> 00:48:36,920
What? How am I supposed to do this?

673
00:48:37,220 --> 00:48:38,221
It hurts so much.

674
00:48:52,836 --> 00:48:54,938
What was that?
Something just went past me.

675
00:49:08,485 --> 00:49:09,553
What was that?

676
00:49:11,488 --> 00:49:12,356
What?

677
00:49:13,357 --> 00:49:14,257
Ma'am.

678
00:49:15,025 --> 00:49:17,260
How do you pick them so easily?

679
00:49:18,662 --> 00:49:19,630
Ma'am.

680
00:49:21,098 --> 00:49:22,032
Did she not hear me?

681
00:49:37,147 --> 00:49:39,483
Ma'am. I'll come over to your side.

682
00:49:43,553 --> 00:49:44,855
Ma'am.

683
00:49:50,294 --> 00:49:51,995
A hearing aid.

684
00:49:53,330 --> 00:49:55,265
I guess you can't hear very well.

685
00:49:55,999 --> 00:49:59,169
I'll watch and learn from you.

686
00:50:08,011 --> 00:50:08,979
I'm sorry.

687
00:50:52,155 --> 00:50:53,123
Who?

688
00:50:54,391 --> 00:50:56,860
You're the scooter girl from earlier.

689
00:50:57,961 --> 00:50:59,630
Oh.

690
00:51:00,163 --> 00:51:03,233
He's from the family that moved here
from Seoul.

691
00:51:03,233 --> 00:51:04,401
And this girl...

692
00:51:04,401 --> 00:51:06,136
She lives next door to yours.

693
00:51:06,136 --> 00:51:07,771
You two are neighbors.

694
00:51:12,609 --> 00:51:13,910
The phone guy.

695
00:51:15,579 --> 00:51:17,648
So what happened to your clothes?

696
00:51:22,719 --> 00:51:23,487
Well...

697
00:51:23,487 --> 00:51:26,023
He looked bored, rolling around
in the field. So we brought him here.

698
00:51:26,590 --> 00:51:29,660
Hey, tall boy. You know what'll happen
if you don't fill that basket, right?

699
00:51:29,660 --> 00:51:31,328
I'll smack you.

700
00:51:31,328 --> 00:51:32,763
I can do a good job.

701
00:51:33,597 --> 00:51:34,564
I'll do my best.

702
00:51:38,135 --> 00:51:38,969
Ow.

703
00:51:39,202 --> 00:51:41,738
- He's useless.
- Goodness.

704
00:51:47,978 --> 00:51:50,847
You've clearly never touched dirt
in your whole life.

705
00:51:51,615 --> 00:51:52,749
Are you a student?

706
00:51:52,749 --> 00:51:54,117
Yes, I'm a college student.

707
00:51:55,052 --> 00:51:57,654
I came down here for a bit with my dad.

708
00:51:58,689 --> 00:52:00,958
A college student came here with his dad.

709
00:52:00,958 --> 00:52:02,392
You're a good son.

710
00:52:02,392 --> 00:52:03,760
I'm only staying a few days.

711
00:52:04,928 --> 00:52:06,763
Oh. I'm Im Bo Mi.

712
00:52:06,763 --> 00:52:08,198
I'm a nutritionist at a school here.

713
00:52:08,198 --> 00:52:10,968
I come and help out in the fields
like this when I have free time.

714
00:52:11,368 --> 00:52:13,637
I'm Seong Ji Cheon.

715
00:52:30,087 --> 00:52:32,656
Right here.
You have to grab the top part here.

716
00:52:33,123 --> 00:52:34,424
Cucumber thorns are sharp,

717
00:52:34,424 --> 00:52:36,093
so even with gloves, it hurts
if you grab too hard.

718
00:52:39,896 --> 00:52:40,931
Like this?

719
00:52:40,931 --> 00:52:42,366
Like this. Like this.

720
00:52:54,444 --> 00:52:56,113
This is where the future begins.

721
00:52:57,848 --> 00:52:59,082
Seong Tae Hun napa cabbage.

722
00:53:00,250 --> 00:53:02,419
Kimchi made
from multi-functional cabbage...

723
00:53:05,088 --> 00:53:07,357
that tastes good and
has anti-cancer properties.

724
00:53:23,273 --> 00:53:24,474
(Napa cabbage variety development
fully suspended)

725
00:53:44,962 --> 00:53:46,964
(Seedling greenhouse)

726
00:53:52,536 --> 00:53:55,405
(Yeonri-ri Project)

727
00:53:56,073 --> 00:53:57,307
Farming isn't complicated.

728
00:53:57,975 --> 00:54:00,978
All I need is land, seeds, and water.

729
00:54:00,978 --> 00:54:01,979
I have everything here.

730
00:54:03,280 --> 00:54:05,782
If you plant it, it'll grow.

731
00:54:12,289 --> 00:54:15,425
If you plant it, it'll grow.

732
00:54:25,602 --> 00:54:28,305
Why isn't this working? Why?

733
00:54:28,305 --> 00:54:30,907
Why won't it work? Why? Why? Why?

734
00:54:30,907 --> 00:54:34,344
It's working. It's working.

735
00:54:44,554 --> 00:54:45,422
It's working.

736
00:54:45,989 --> 00:54:47,958
It's working. It's working. It's working.

737
00:55:14,918 --> 00:55:17,721
Yes. I can do this.

738
00:55:17,721 --> 00:55:20,257
I will go back to Seoul...

739
00:55:20,257 --> 00:55:22,526
with my wife and kids!

740
00:55:23,327 --> 00:55:26,697
I'm going back.

741
00:55:27,998 --> 00:55:30,667
You seem full of energy.
What are you doing here?

742
00:55:31,368 --> 00:55:33,837
Chief. I'm farming.

743
00:55:34,738 --> 00:55:37,574
This isn't even your own plot.

744
00:55:37,874 --> 00:55:39,710
You got demoted so this is your hobby now?

745
00:55:41,044 --> 00:55:43,580
I wasn't demoted.

746
00:55:44,348 --> 00:55:45,882
I understand why you think that,

747
00:55:45,882 --> 00:55:48,552
but I came here to develop napa cabbage...

748
00:55:48,552 --> 00:55:50,187
that only Mat Story can produce.

749
00:55:50,621 --> 00:55:51,455
Napa cabbage?

750
00:55:53,023 --> 00:55:54,024
Napa cabbage farming?

751
00:55:54,558 --> 00:55:55,592
Yes.

752
00:55:55,592 --> 00:55:56,927
Napa cabbage with consistent sugar levels,

753
00:55:56,927 --> 00:55:58,762
and specialized nutrients,

754
00:55:58,762 --> 00:56:00,263
grown organically,

755
00:56:00,263 --> 00:56:02,099
and made into a specialty product
of Yeonri-ri...

756
00:56:02,099 --> 00:56:05,235
So Mat Story napa cabbage will
become a local specialty?

757
00:56:05,569 --> 00:56:07,838
Yes, exactly.

758
00:56:08,105 --> 00:56:10,173
I'll call it Seong Tae Hun cabbage...

759
00:56:10,173 --> 00:56:11,241
Have...

760
00:56:12,709 --> 00:56:14,378
Have some shame.

761
00:56:14,378 --> 00:56:16,847
You're basically a slave
to a big corporation, aren't you?

762
00:56:16,847 --> 00:56:17,881
Chief.

763
00:56:18,282 --> 00:56:19,950
That's a bit harsh, don't you think?

764
00:56:19,950 --> 00:56:21,118
Harsh?

765
00:56:21,785 --> 00:56:23,987
You showed up looking like a beggar
in this heat,

766
00:56:23,987 --> 00:56:26,556
so I even helped you find a house,

767
00:56:26,556 --> 00:56:27,958
and now listen to the nonsense
you're spouting.

768
00:56:28,558 --> 00:56:31,495
I was going to let it go because
I made mistakes, too,

769
00:56:31,495 --> 00:56:34,231
but do you even have
a real estate license?

770
00:56:34,231 --> 00:56:36,166
Showing houses without a license...

771
00:56:36,166 --> 00:56:37,734
is fraud.

772
00:56:37,734 --> 00:56:39,403
A real estate license?
I'm glad you mentioned it.

773
00:56:39,403 --> 00:56:41,471
What about you?
Do you have a farming license?

774
00:56:42,239 --> 00:56:44,641
Why would I need a license to farm?

775
00:56:44,641 --> 00:56:46,343
Yes, you do.

776
00:56:46,944 --> 00:56:49,246
Because farming is something
done by people.

777
00:56:49,579 --> 00:56:51,882
But Mat Story isn't people.

778
00:56:51,882 --> 00:56:53,951
It's a beast that killed this land.

779
00:56:54,518 --> 00:56:56,853
How can you say this land is dead?

780
00:56:58,221 --> 00:57:01,124
You left this fine land abandoned for
ten years and killed it.

781
00:57:01,525 --> 00:57:03,994
Clear away the rocks if you want.
See if a blade of grass will grow.

782
00:57:03,994 --> 00:57:06,863
I used to be a researcher.
I know what to do.

783
00:57:06,863 --> 00:57:08,565
No, you don't.

784
00:57:09,199 --> 00:57:11,835
I'll make sure you can't do anything here.

785
00:57:12,336 --> 00:57:14,271
That's ridiculous.

786
00:57:14,271 --> 00:57:15,706
How can you possibly do that?

787
00:57:17,941 --> 00:57:18,875
Tell me.

788
00:57:19,343 --> 00:57:20,377
What do you think...

789
00:57:20,844 --> 00:57:21,912
you can do on your own here...

790
00:57:22,346 --> 00:57:23,614
without me?

791
00:57:53,010 --> 00:57:54,278
Village...

792
00:57:55,646 --> 00:57:56,980
chief!

793
00:58:39,222 --> 00:58:42,793
Like being struck by lightning
and splashed with water.

794
00:58:42,793 --> 00:58:43,627
Yes.

795
00:58:44,194 --> 00:58:45,562
That could happen in life.

796
00:58:46,196 --> 00:58:47,764
It happens.

797
00:58:47,764 --> 00:58:52,135
But why does it have to be me?

798
00:59:01,912 --> 00:59:04,348
(We thank Min Sung Wuk
for his special appearance)

799
00:59:25,535 --> 00:59:28,538
(Cabbage Your Life)

800
00:59:28,538 --> 00:59:31,975
Send 1,500 seedling samples
within a month.

801
00:59:33,343 --> 00:59:35,345
Why won't it grow? Why?

802
00:59:36,179 --> 00:59:38,348
Mr. Seong Ji Cheon.

803
00:59:39,016 --> 00:59:40,217
I'm Officer Park Soon Kyung.

804
00:59:40,217 --> 00:59:41,151
Easy to remember, right?

805
00:59:43,053 --> 00:59:45,088
I officially declare this
as the village chief.

806
00:59:45,088 --> 00:59:47,791
Do not help Seong Tae Hun at all.

807
00:59:47,791 --> 00:59:49,326
Village chief's official stamp.

808
00:59:49,326 --> 00:59:50,727
Get a recommendation from
the village chief.

809
00:59:50,727 --> 00:59:52,896
Village chief. Village chief.
Village chief.

810
00:59:52,896 --> 00:59:55,332
I'll deal with
the Women's Association first.

811
00:59:55,332 --> 00:59:56,667
Hello.

812
00:59:57,301 --> 00:59:58,502
Let's find a way.

813
00:59:58,502 --> 01:00:00,270
If there's no proper way,
I'll find another way.

814
01:00:03,340 --> 01:00:05,342
(Subtitles are provided by KOCOWA.)

